sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Utilisateur
    participant Front as Frontend Demoboard
    participant API as API service
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant Redis as Redis queue
    participant Worker as Worker service
    participant OTEL as OTEL Collector / LGTM

    rect rgb(236, 245, 242)
        note over User,PG: 1. Creation d'une task
        User->>Front: Saisit une nouvelle task
        Front->>API: POST /tasks {title}
        activate API
        API->>API: Span HTTP + span tasks.create
        API->>PG: INSERT INTO tasks(title,status='pending')
        PG-->>API: id, title, status='pending'
        API->>OTEL: metrics API + trace + logs JSON
        API-->>Front: 201 Created {id, pending}
        deactivate API
        Front-->>User: Affiche la task pending
    end

    rect rgb(247, 239, 226)
        note over User,Redis: 2. Lancement du traitement asynchrone
        User->>Front: Clique "lancer traitement"
        Front->>API: POST /tasks/{id}/start-job
        activate API
        API->>API: Span HTTP + span tasks.start_job
        API->>PG: UPDATE tasks SET status='processing' WHERE id=:id
        PG-->>API: OK
        API->>API: inject(carrier) dans le contexte courant OTEL
        API->>Redis: RPUSH jobs {"task_id": id, "_trace": carrier}
        API->>API: Span redis.publish_job
        API->>OTEL: metrics job_start + trace API + logs
        API-->>Front: 200 OK {"message":"Job started"}
        deactivate API
        Front-->>User: Affiche la task processing
    end

    rect rgb(238, 240, 251)
        note over Redis,Worker: 3. Traitement par le worker
        Worker->>Redis: BLPOP jobs
        Redis-->>Worker: {"task_id": id, "_trace": carrier}
        activate Worker
        Worker->>Worker: extract(_trace)
        Worker->>Worker: Span worker.process_job parenté à la trace API
        Worker->>Worker: Simulation du traitement
        alt Node/AZ degradee
            Worker->>Worker: Latence 3.5s a 6s
            Worker->>OTEL: logs warning "retry processing step"
        else Node normal
            Worker->>Worker: Latence 1.5s a 2.7s
        end
        Worker->>PG: UPDATE tasks SET status='completed' WHERE id=:id
        PG-->>Worker: OK
        Worker->>Worker: Span worker.complete_task
        Worker->>OTEL: histogram worker duration + exemplars + trace + logs
        deactivate Worker
    end

    rect rgb(247, 239, 226)
        note over User,PG: 4. Lecture de l'etat final
        Front->>API: GET /tasks
        activate API
        API->>API: Span tasks.list
        API->>PG: SELECT id,title,status FROM tasks ORDER BY id
        PG-->>API: Liste des tasks
        API->>OTEL: metrics API + trace + logs
        API-->>Front: 200 OK [..., completed]
        deactivate API
        Front-->>User: Affiche la task completed
    end

    rect rgb(245, 232, 232)
        note over User,PG: 5. Suppression de la task
        User->>Front: Clique "supprimer"
        Front->>API: DELETE /tasks/{id}
        activate API
        API->>API: Span HTTP + span tasks.delete
        API->>PG: DELETE FROM tasks WHERE id=:id
        PG-->>API: rowcount=1
        API->>OTEL: metrics API DELETE 204 + trace + logs
        API-->>Front: 204 No Content
        deactivate API
        Front-->>User: Retire la task de la liste
    end

    note over OTEL: Tous les spans d'une action partagent un trace_id. Les logs contiennent trace_id/span_id. Les histogrammes API/worker peuvent porter des exemplars vers Tempo.
